From: Nikami Worlds Harness <nikami-worlds@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 21:05:00 -0700
Subject: [EXPERIMENT] ESM4 actor attachment matrix telemetry

Status: experiment, not listed in patches/openmw/series.

Evidence basis:
- run/proof-harness-sweeps/20260707-205427 showed part-space samples but no
  frame-level attachment/surface matrix samples.
- run/proof-harness-sweeps/20260707-210134 confirmed frame-level part telemetry
  for FO3/FNV current and auto modes, but proof still failed because runtime,
  rig pose, and visual review remained red.

Purpose:
- Add measurement-only final attachment matrix telemetry for head-relative ESM4
  actor parts.
- This is a diagnostic patch only. It must not be promoted as a visual actor fix.

diff --git a/apps/openmw/mwrender/esm4npcanimation.cpp b/apps/openmw/mwrender/esm4npcanimation.cpp
index 0000000000..0000000000 100644
--- a/apps/openmw/mwrender/esm4npcanimation.cpp
+++ b/apps/openmw/mwrender/esm4npcanimation.cpp
@@ -6043,13 +6043,51 @@ namespace MWRender
         if (attached != nullptr)
         {
             MarkFalloutRigGeometryVisitor markFalloutRigs;
